Privacy Policy — “Word of the Day” SMS Service

Effective Date: July 8, 2026

1) Who we are

This Privacy Policy explains how Jack Everett Koss collect, use, and protect information when you sign up to receive “Word of the Day” text messages by SMS.

2) What information we collect

We collect and process your phone number in order to deliver the SMS messages you request (“Word of the Day”).

We do not collect the following as part of this service:

Email addresses
Names
Payment or billing information
Message content beyond delivery of the requested “Word of the Day” texts
Other personal data unless you provide it voluntarily for support purposes
3) How we use your information

We use your phone number solely to:

Send the scheduled “Word of the Day” SMS messages
Manage your subscription status (e.g., responding to opt-out requests)
4) Sharing and disclosure of information

We do not sell, rent, or trade your phone number.
We do not share your phone number with third parties except as necessary to deliver SMS messages (e.g., with a service provider that helps send messages), and those providers are required to use your information only for the purpose of delivering the service.

5) Data retention

We retain your phone number only as long as necessary to provide the SMS service to you. If you opt out, we will stop sending messages and remove your phone number from active lists within a reasonable time.

6) Your choices (opt-out)

You can opt out at any time by replying:

STOP to unsubscribe
After you opt out, we will discontinue SMS messages to that number.

7) Security

We take reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures designed to protect your phone number from unauthorized access, misuse, or disclosure.

8) Children

This service is intended for general audiences and is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

9) Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will update the “Effective Date” above.

10) Contact us

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact: support@jackkoss.org.
